02/02/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Demographic Research Centre of the Romanian Academy is forecasting alarming trends about the size and structure of the country's population, according to an article Monday (2 February) in <I>Nine o'Clock</I>. The centre expects the population to decline from 21 million last year to 20 million in 2025. At the same time, the researchers estimate a serious ageing of the population. In addition, Romania has one of the highest mortality rates in Europe.
In other news, Romania's sports agency said Monday that the country is willing to team up with Hungary to host the 2012 European Soccer Championship. The Romanian government reportedly supports the project but no final decision has been made. (Nine o'Clock, Rompres - 02/02/04)
